1.title: Dirty Deeds
1.plot: Walter hijacks Dennis's tree house with some fake deeds.

2.title: Last Day of Summer
2.plot: Dennis is consigned to a day of hard labour stacking logs as punishment for pranking the Colonel.

3.title: You and Whose Army
3.plot: The Colonel's arch rival comes to Beanotown.

4.title: Menace's Seven
4.plot: Dennis assembles a crack team to bust into the Headmaster's confiscation cupboard.

5.title: Dinmakers Go Ape
5.plot: Dennis and The Dinmakers recruit a gorilla disguised as their new lead singer to enter a Battle of the Bands.

6.title: The Ultimate Prank
6.plot: Dennis spreads the word around Beanotown that he is planning the ultimate prank.

7.title: I'll Teach You
7.plot: Mrs Creecher goes on holiday - permanently - and Dennis's Mum is recruited as the new substitute teacher.

8.title: Hairy Plotter
8.plot: Some experimental hair restorer turns Dad into a Gorilla - and the rest of Beanotown into one giant bad hair day.

9.title: Bring the Din
9.plot: The Din Makers borrow Gran's menaced-up amp and accidentally create a bass induced earthquake in Beanotown.

10.title: The Exterminator
10.plot: The menaces disguise Gnasher as a giant ant to trick the exterminator into closing the school for the day.

11.title: Late for School
11.plot: Dennis and Walter try to make each other late for school.

12.title: The Gnashinator
12.plot: A shadowy government agency copy Gnasher's teeth to make a secret weapon, with disastrous results.

13.title: Sick as a Parrot
13.plot: Dennis has to look after the school's pet parrot.

14.title: Dennis's School Dinners
14.plot: Dennis and co masquerade as school dinner ladies.

15.title: Escape from Detention
15.plot: Dennis and co bust out of detention to attend to some pranking.

16.title: Come Menace With Me
16.plot: Dennis and his parents are 'invited' to Walter's house for dinner.

17.title: Leg Cuffed
17.plot: Dennis ends up permanently attached to Walter following the 3 legged race at the school sports day.

18.title: Piranharama
18.plot: Dennis decides to get a pet piranha pal for Gnasher.

19.title: Way of the Tiger
19.plot: A tiger escapes from Beanotown zoo.

20.title: Stunt Gran
20.plot: Walter and Gran have a skate-off.

21.title: Just Desserts
21.plot: Dennis and co organise an elaborate pie heist in the school canteen.

22.title: Couldn't Catch a Cold
22.plot: Dennis tries to catch a cold to get a coveted day off school.

23.title: No Match for Dennis
23.plot: Dennis and Walter challenge each other to a game of football.

24.title: The Greatest Dog in the World
24.plot: Gnasher has a crisis of confidence, so Dennis and co menace up an impromptu 'space mission' to restore his mojo.

25.title: Car Wash Caper
25.plot: Dennis starts a car wash to pay off a damages bill - and invents a remote-controlled fake-pooping bird to drum up business.

26.title: Sausage Suspect
26.plot: The World's Largest Sausage arrives in Beanotown - but when the banger gets a bite in it, Gnasher is the prime suspect.

27.title: Special Delivery
27.plot: An experimental robot postman puts the postie out of a job - and robs Gnasher of his favourite sparring partner.

28.title: Photo Finish
28.plot: It's school photo day, and Dennis has been ordered to stay squeaky clean for the perfect portrait.

29.title: The Way the Cookie Crumble
29.plot: Dennis and Walter go head to head to win the prize for selling the most cookies during a school fundraiser.

30.title: Menace Camp
30.plot: Dennis and his family go on a camping holiday - only to find Walter and his Uncle in charge of the campsite.

31.title: Sw... itched!
31.plot: Gnasher and Claude mysteriously switch personalities after Gnasher's bath-time goes even more wrong than usual.

32.title: Constable Menace
32.plot: Dennis is assigned to Sgt Slipper's command for 'Take A Kid To Work Day', when reports start flooding in of gnome thefts all over Beanotown.

33.title: The Book of the Menace
33.plot: Dennis's worst nightmare comes true when Walter finds a hand-written journal called The Book of The Menace, literally containing every trick in the book.

34.title: I Fought the Lawn
34.plot: Dennis and co concoct a super plant food to speed up their homework of growing cress - but end up with an overgrown lawn, and some errant water-cress hybrids with an insatiable appetite.

35.title: Menace Swap
35.plot: After Dennis and Walter mess up a science experiment, De Testa issues the rivals with a formidable challenge - they must swap lives for the day.

36.title: Pie Protectors
36.plot: When a new patisserie threatens to close down Pieface's Dad's pie shop, he issues a challenge: whoever can cook the tastiest pie wins; and the loser has to shut up shop.

37.title: Curse of the Menace
37.plot: Dennis pranks an exhibition opening and accidentally breaks open an ancient Egyptian sarcophagus, paving the way for an epic double bluff as Walter convinces the town they are the victims of an evil curse.

38.title: the Omega Menace
38.plot: Walter and co challenge Dennis and co to a card strategy game called Omega Flip - and the losing gang have to be butlers to the winners for a whole month.

39.title: The Daily Menace
39.plot: Dennis and Walter set up rival newspapers and battle it out to win the final remaining press pass for the Beanotown Cup Final.

40.title: Bone Free Zone
40.plot: Gnasher's bone collection is mistaken for a new archaeological discovery and taken into custody by a famous palaeontologist.

41.title: Bona Fide Genius
41.plot: Beanotown school gets a visit from the world's toughest school inspector, Derek Pencils.

42.title: The Mayor Affair
42.plot: Mayor Scrimp bans skateboarding on the eve of the mayoral election, prompting the menaces to sabotage his campaign - but then Walter's Dad is elected in his place.

43.title: The Show Mustn't Go On
43.plot: Dennis's elaborate excuses catch the attention of actor Blake Midwinter - and he ends up as the lead in the school play - unfortunately, it's a romantic lead.

44.title: The Walterslide
44.plot: The menaces build the world's most ambitious waterslide to get past Walter's state of the art pool security system: the Poolboy 2.0.

45.title: Prom Mean
45.plot: The menaces are horrified to learn that the end of term trip to the adventure playground has been replaced with a School Prom - and worse still, Dennis is roped in to helping organize it as a punishment.

46.title: Beanotown 5000
46.plot: The menaces take on Walter, and the rest of the town, in the Beanotown 5000 - a no-holds-barred go-kart race down Mt Beano.

47.title: Doggy Daycare
47.plot: Mum books Gnipper into the Palace of Doggy Delights for the night - but the menaces discover it's more like a doggy prison.

48.title: Pranks for the Memories
48.plot: Dennis and Gnasher go head to head with Gran in the ultimate battle of the menaces.

49.title: Itchin' for Gnasher
49.plot: Great Aunt Flic comes to visit Dennis - but she's terrified of fleas, so the menaces make a fake Gnasher to re-house them. Temporarily.

50.title: Triathlon Trouble
50.plot: Dennis, Walter and Angel Face are forced together to face rival school Greytown Prep in the annual Triathlon Competition.

51.title: Perfect Prefect
51.plot: Dennis discovers that the class prefect is allowed to bring a pet to school, and resolves to get an unlikely menace elected.

52.title: Tank You Very Much
52.plot: The Colonel has a shiny new tank called Monty, and Dennis is determined to have a ride in it - but he'll have to rescue it from the scrap yard first.

imdb.title: Dennis & Gnasher
plot: Dennis the Menace gets up to extreme fun and mischief with his friends, Pieface and Curly.::Anonymous
